Step 1: Download the Dataset

Open this link: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1W-88FKdbZ3BMzgz1HWa-RKk4t5OWPuji/view
Click the Download button (top right)
Save the file as Dataset-SA.csv


Step 2: Set Up Your Project Folder
Create a folder and place both files inside it:
my_project/
├── main.py             ← the FastAPI file you downloaded
├── requirements.txt    ← the requirements file you downloaded
└── Dataset-SA.csv      ← the dataset you just downloaded

Step 3: Install Python
Make sure you have Python 3.10 or 3.11 installed.
Check with:
bashpython --version
If not installed, download from https://www.python.org/downloads/

Step 4: Create a Virtual Environment
Open a terminal inside your project folder and run:
bash# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# Activate it — Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate

# Activate it — Mac/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate
You'll see (venv) appear in your terminal. That means it's active.

Step 5: Install Dependencies
bashpip install -r requirements.txt
This installs FastAPI, TensorFlow, scikit-learn, NLTK, and everything else. It may take 2–5 minutes.

