## Step 7: Open the Swagger UI (Interactive Docs)

Open your browser and go to:
```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
This gives you a full interactive interface to test every endpoint — no extra tools needed.

Step 8: Train the Models
This is the most important first step before using any other endpoint.
In the Swagger UI:

Click POST /train
Click "Try it out"
Paste this into the request body:

json{
  "csv_path": "Dataset-SA.csv",
  "train_lstm": false
}

Click Execute


Training takes 1–3 minutes. When done, you'll see accuracy scores in the response.

If you also want the LSTM model trained (takes 5–10 extra minutes), set "train_lstm": true.

Step 9: Use the Endpoints
Predict Sentiment
Click POST /predict/sentiment → Try it out → paste:
json{
  "review": "This product is absolutely amazing, works perfectly!"
}
Predict Star Rating
Click POST /predict/rating → Try it out → paste:
json{
  "review": "Stopped working after 2 days, very disappointed."
}
Check Urgency Score
Click POST /urgency → Try it out → paste:
json{
  "review": "Terrible quality, complete scam, I want a return!"
}
Dataset Stats
Click GET /eda/stats → Try it out → Execute (no body needed)
Top Words
Click GET /eda/top-words → Try it out → set n=20 → Execute
Compare LR vs LSTM
Click GET /model/comparison → Try it out → Execute
(LSTM column will be null if you didn't train it)
